\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Note Note
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
In the following, I am basically copying the package documentation to make
 the code understandable for later.
 Would maybe be better with a Rmarkdown file, but would that be useful?.
\end_layout

\end_inset

The quadratic programming algorithm aims at finding 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}$
\end_inset

 that minimizes 
\begin_inset Formula $||\mathbf{Cx}-\mathbf{d}||^{2}$
\end_inset

 under the constraints 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{Ex}=\mathbf{f}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{Gx}>=\mathbf{h}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{C}=\mathbf{I}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{d}=[\text{vec(\ensuremath{\mathbf{A}^{T})}}^{\frown}\mathbf{r'}]$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{A}$
\end_inset

 is the interaction matrix, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{r'}=-(\text{e}^{\mathbf{r}}-\mathbb{\mathbb{\mathbf{1}}})$
\end_inset

 is the vector of growth rates, 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{E}$
\end_inset

 is built so that we verify the equality 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{AN^{*}+r'}=0$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{N}^{*}$
\end_inset

is the vector of abundance at equilibrium (more precisely, here, average
 abundance values over the whole time series), and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{G},\mathbf{h}$
\end_inset

 so that 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{r}>0$
\end_inset

 (genera have a positive growth rate when taken in isolation) and 
\begin_inset Formula $\forall i,a_{ii}>0$
\end_inset

 (negative density-dependence, individuals from the same genus compete with
 each other).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
NOTE: This may not be useful as only the mean growth rate can be used to
 adjust the model (due to its dependence on the temperature), and the calibratio
n of the interaction matrix tends to lead to a stable community, that is
 not able to represent the yearly cycles due to seasonality.
 
\end_layout

